<file:///workdir/tmprdf/data/53/DE/D7/53DED76BA3735A4C91EA80D346122343.rdf>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Photographs of some specimens of Bothriechis supraciliaris in life. a, d, e. From Reptilandia, Costa Rica; and b, c. From a private collection in Costa Rica. Photos by Jose Vieira.", "Figure 11. Hemipenial architecture of Bothriechis supraciliaris in sulcate, lateral, and asulcate views. a. UTA R- 35246 from Jardin Botanico Las Cruces, Puntarenas province, Costa Rica; b. UTA R- 35192 from Jardin Botanico Las Cruces, Puntarenas province, Costa Rica. Photos by Eric N. Smith.", "Figure 3. Distribution of species of Bothriechis previously subsumed under B. schlegelii sensu lato. Each colored area is a geographic representation of the suitable environmental conditions for one of the clades recovered in the phylogeny of Fig. 2. Lime green shade in southeastern Panama represents overlap between between B. nigroadspersus and B. torvus.", "Figure 9. Adult female holotype of Bothriechis supraciliaris KU 31997 in a. Dorsal and b. Ventral view. Photos by Hannah Som." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/981689", "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/981695", "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/981696", "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/981697" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

